    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. you say it was a \"textbook example of a strategic failure,\" but wouldn't a realist argue that the primary goal of regime change was achieved? if the goal was simply to remove a destabilizing leader, isn't it a bit reductive to call the whole thing a failure just because the aftermath was messy?",
