      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pursuit of perfect, stable democracies through military intervention is a naive and dangerous ideal that ignores geopolitical reality. A successful intervention must prioritize immediate security objectives, such as preventing mass atrocities or stopping the proliferation of dangerous actors. If the intervention achieves that primary, measurable security goal, it is a success, regardless of the messy, long-term political fallout.",
